ASSIGNMENT 

Title: Secure Multi-User Project Setup
Objective:
 Design a secure Linux environment for a team working on a shared project.
Scenario:
You are a DevOps engineer managing a shared server where multiple developers collaborate. You must ensure proper ownership, permissions, and security.
Tasks:
Create three users: dev1, dev2, dev3
Create a group named projectteam
Add all users to the group
Create a directory /project
Assign ownership of the directory appropriately
Ensure that all files created inside /project inherit the same group
Create a script file inside the directory
Set permissions such that:
Only the owner can modify the file
Group members can read and execute
Others have no access
Test access by switching between users
Simulate a permission error and resolve it
Questions:
How is ownership determined when files are created?
Why is group-based access control important?
What problems can occur with incorrect permissions?
How can you ensure group inheritance in directories?
What security risks arise from overly permissive access?
